, to sparking revolutions in Tunisia, Egypt, and Libya, the waithood generation, as we are reminded in The Time of Youth, is using its resources redress the wrongs of contemporary society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAfrica -- Economic conditions -- 21st century. 0aAfrica -- Social conditions -- 21st century. 0aUnemployed youth -- Africa. 0aUnemployed youthzAfrica. 0aYoung adults -- Africa -- Economic conditions -- 21st century. 0aYoung adults -- Africa -- Social conditions -- 21st century. 0aYoung adults -- Employment -- Africa. 0aYoung adultsxEmploymentzAfrica. 0aYoung adultszAfricaxEconomic conditionsy21st century. 0aYoung adultszAfricaxSocial conditionsy21st century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978156549473240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781565494732423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781565494732/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles